china has purged 153000 people from its 
communist party over the past five years and disciplined another 
656000 as part of a drive to improve the quality of its members 
the government announced today 
in addition the partys central committee organization 
department said the party last year accepted only one out of four 
applicants for membership in the elite group which rules china 
the party took in 2 million new members last year out of 8 
million applicants bringing total membership to 4775 million the 
official xinhua news agency said about 1 billion people live in 
china 
