violence during the school desegregation years his neighbors have 
criticized him severely for his support of desegregated public 
housing 
i am asking the people of boston for their personal support 
flynn said 
under the agreement the housing authority would identify people 
who have been victims of discriminatory public housing practices 
and place them near the top of the priority housing list only 
emergency cases such as a family on the verge of homelessness 
would receive a higher priority for receiving a unit 
anyone passed over because of race or national origin since oct 
1 1983 would be considered such a victim 
flynn emphasized that no current resident of public housing 
would be forced to move as a result of the agreement 
bostons housing authority is the largest in the country to 
