<TEXT>
flu shots are a good idea for aids victims other 
highrisk patients and those who will be taking care of them during 
next years flu season federal health officials said 
the recommendation by the immunization practices advisory 
committee was among updated influenza information contained in 
thursdays weekly report from the centers for disease control 
the committee targeted people with immunosuppression or the 
squelching of natural responses that produce immunity such as what 
occurs with aids as being at moderate risk of flurelated 
complications but suggested that people who care for them take 
extra precautions if a flu strain is present in the community 
especially during the twoweek period between the time a flu shot 
is administered and the time it takes effect 
the committee also recommended that the drug amantadine which 
has been shown to reduce the severity and duration of typea flu 
strains be used with highrisk patients when an outbreak of 
influenza a is present cdc epidemiologist nancy arden said 
the flu vaccine is particularly recommended for people who are 
at high risk for having serious complications or dying if they get 
the flu she said but the vaccine may not produce a higher 
level of antibodies with immunosuppresive persons than with people 
with a healthier immune system 
physicians nurses family members and others who have extensive 
contact with such patients could use amantadine if they have not 
received an influenza vaccine or in the interim until a vaccine 
takes effect ms arden said 
amantadine is recommended for people taking care of highrisk 
patients if they have not taken the vaccine she said another 
strategy is when influenza develops in the community people who 
havent gotten the vaccine can go to a physician and get a 
prescription for amantadine and that way they are protected 
during the time they are developing an antibody response to the 
vaccine 
ms arden cautioned however that the use of amantadine is not 
viable for all patients and physicians should evaluate its use on 
an individual basis 
