in a twist on a tactic generally used to 
increase black representation birminghams white minority has won 
a ruling allowing it to challenge atlarge local elections for 
allegedly diluting white votes 
similar suits filed by blacks have thrown out atlarge election 
systems in many other cities as violations of the 1965 voting 
rights act 
us district judge robert b propst signed a ruling thursday 
