out of azerbaijan the legislature asked its azerbaijani 
counterpart to approve the switch and the central supreme soviet in 
moscow to give its approval 
central communist party officials in moscow rejected the 
annexation demand in february but the central supreme soviet has 
not reviewed the issue 
gerasimov also said students had ended a sitin they had 
launched may 25 in armenias capital yerevan soviet newspapers 
however have reported this week that unrest continues in 
stepanakert the main city of nagornokarabakh armenians in the 
city have been marching and striking since may 23 
the soviet government made nagornokarabakh an autonomous region 
of azerbaijan in 1923 
armenians are predominantly christian most azerbaijanis are 
moslem 
