<TEXT>
cher the actress and entertainer once 
performed in south africa but has been taken off a list kept by the 
un antiapartheid agency because she promised not to do so again 
the list contains the names of more than 200 performers and 
members of related professions who have worked in south africa 
since 1981 a person can be taken off by promising in writing not 
to perform there while the government practices the apartheid 
policy of race segregation 
the sixth annual list will be published next month frank 
