federal authorities have revised their 
charges against fallen carpetcleaning whiz kid barry minkow by 
filing a superseding indictment that adds conspiracy and 
creditcard fraud counts to the original case 
the revised 57count indictment filed thursday names the 
22yearold minkow and three other defendants as participants in an 
alleged conspiracy to commit securities fraud obtain funds 
fraudulently and falsify legal documents 
the new indictment also alleges that minkows illegal conduct 
began when the entrepreneur who founded the zzzz best 
carpetcleaning empire was 18 years old at least two years 
earlier than previously disclosed 
an added count of credit card fraud alleges that as early as 
october 1984 minkow devised and participated in a scheme to 
defraud by making unauthorized charges to creditcard numbers of 
zzzz best customers 
minkow allegedly obtained more than 29800 from 16 customers 
through the creditcard scheme 
minkows defense attorney david kenner could not immediately 
be reached for comment but at a news conference a week ago kenner 
declared that his client was a fall guy nothing more than a 
stepchild of organized crime 
a racketeering count which carried a 20year maximum sentence 
has been deleted from the new charges 
assistant us attorney james asperger said the racketeering 
count allowed federal authorities to seize minkows assets but 
asperger said those assets have become tied up in us bankruptcy 
court 
the prosecutor said the revised indictment increases the maximum 
prison term minkow faces if convicted from 350 years to 403 years 
the original indictment which was unsealed jan 15 charged 
minkow and 10 other defendants with 54 counts of bank fraud money 
laundering tax fraud and racketeering a 12th defendant was named 
in a separate complaint 
most of the previously filed counts are included in the new 
case although all but the four remaining defendants have pleaded 
guilty or are expected to do so before trial 
minkow founded his zzzz best carpetcleaning company in his 
parents garage in suburban reseda when he was just 15 
four years later in 1985 he incorporated the business and the 
zzzz best co became a publicly traded firm in the overthecounter 
market in january 1986 
however the revised indictment alleges that as early as march 
1985 minkow and other defendants falsely claimed zzzz best was 
performing restoration work on buildings damaged by water fire and 
other causes 
at its height the restoration work purportedly comprised over 
90 percent or 437 million of zzzz bests annual revenues the 
indictment states in fact zzzz best performed virtually no 
restoration work 
