federal judge ruling the grandson of the companys founder cannot 
use his own name as a trademark 
gucci is barred from designing and selling merchandise under the 
company name paolo gucci as he has in the past the judge said 
but us district judge william c conner in a 33page 
decision ruled paolo gucci can attach his name to other 
trademarked products 
paolos name can follow an existing trademark for example 
american tourister luggage by paolo gucci the judge wrote but 
his name cannot be more prominent than the trademark and there 
must be a disclaimer that he does not work for gucci conner said 
it is clear that if paolo gucci were to continue to use 
his name as a trademark or a trade name an appreciable number of 
consumers would confuse his goods with those of the defendant 
conner wrote in his ruling 
an attorney for gucci shops inc which has 21 stores around 
